Quinoa & Chocolate ‘CRUNCH’ bites. Like Hershey’s Crunch Bars - but better! 😉🍫
.
You’re gonna toast cooked quinoa in the oven - this gets them nice and CRISPY - Toss in your favorite melted chocolate, dollop of coconut oil, nuts if you wish, and that’s it! The non-negotiable is topping with sea salt before you let them set in the fridge/freezer. 🤤🤤🤤
.
Directions:
1️⃣Cook 1/2 Cup of quinoa according to the package; let it cook on a sheet pan lined with parchment paper. 
2️⃣Spray and roast on 400, 10-15 mins until crispy and golden brown. Tossing a few times in the oven to rotate. 
3️⃣Melt about a cup or so of chocolate chips (I used @lilys_sweets )+ a dollop of coconut oil. 
4️⃣Toss the toasted quinoa into the chcoclatw mixed and combine. I also added pumpkin seeds at this point (optional, but worth it).
5️⃣Place dollops of the mixture on another baking sheet lined with parchment paper into preferred bite size pieces. PLEASE SPRINKLE THEM WITH SEA SALT! Set in the freezer to mold. At least 15 mins.
.
Store in the fridge or freezer when you want a sweet & delicious treat! 🍫 Tag a gal if you make them @ericabatterman xoxo
.
.

Prob not what you think! 😂⬇️
.
Guys, the past 11 months have turned our lives upside down in more ways than one, but we are still kicking! 🙃💪 If you didn’t know, here are the bullet points:
.
✔️August 2022, Brent underwent major/urgent open heart surgery. He’s currently fully recovered and his heart and health is on point, thank goodness.
✔️January 2023, I was diagnosed with Breast Cancer. I have since then had surgery, completed treatment (radiation), and now on hormonal meds for the next 5 years if all goes well. Overall thriving, thank goodness again.
✔️The latest: just a week after my final treatment, Brent’s job unexpectedly closed its doors. He found an amazing new opportunity that he’s super excited about… in Tampa, FL.
.
Brent will be living in Tampa, while I hold down the fort in the Fort. 😉 We’ll be splitting our time between the two cities, making the most of every chance to be together. It’s been a rollercoaster to say the least, and all we want now is some SMOOTH sailing! ⛵️🙏
.
Overall, we remain grateful for the countless blessings in our lives, our furry little family, and are immensely fortunate to have such incredible support from our family and friends throughout the past year.
.
To be fair, I have cried, b*tched, questioned, and cried some more on all levels on ALL the above! I have learned so much in the past year, still learning, and I would say the biggest takeaway: LIFE HAS ITS OWN AGENDA. Bad news for a planner like me. 🤭 Staying positive, expressing gratitude, choosing to find happiness, giving myself grace, not treating my body like a dumpster, and not stressing out as much has been my focus - things I can control - a work in progress. It’s been hard, but in someways I also feel stronger and better for all of it. Life is just wild and you need to buckle up big time.
.
Wanted to share our latest update with this community. It means so much that you are here. The good news is, I will have extra time to create and share. That’s the plan anyway. ☺️ 
.
Thanks again for being here. Love y’all. Xoxo
.
.
.
📸: @stefani.kovacevic.photography 
#bowlobsessed #lifeisanadventure #lifeisgood #lifeupdate #newjourney

I’ve been under the weather since I got home from Maine - that calls for this #onepot nourishing Stewed Lentils! ✨ Lentils are highly nutritious and a staple in my pantry when I want a quick fiber/protein add. I have made a version of this SO many times..it’s different every time. 🫢 This round was inspired by @chiefspicemama ‘Dynamite Black Lentils’ - I’ve never added beets before and it was delicious. Thanks for the inspo!
.
Here’s my remake of Kanchan’s recipe:
3 large carrots, chopped
3 prepared mini beets, cubed (bought cooked that come in a package)
1/2 red onion, chopped
1 Cup rinsed lentils
2 cloves garlic, minced
Spoonful of Garam Masala
Spoonful of Curry
1.5 Cup bone broth
 Pink salt and pepper to taste
Sour cream & cilantro to finish
.
Start by sautéing onions in cooking oil/butter for 5 mins. Add carrots and prepared beets another few minutes. Then add garlic, spices, lentils, broth and bring to a boil. Simmer until cooked down, 8-10 mins.
.
Top with sour cream and cilantro. Enjoy!
.
.

💫HOMEMADE CURRIED HUMMUS💫
.
Thank you to @strollmonticello Magazine for the feature!
.
PRO-TIP: The secret to silky smooth hummus: BOIL the chickpeas in water for 10 mins until the chickpeas are soft and skins begin to float! Hummus is one of my favorite healthy snacks & can be made in 20 minutes or less; served with fresh vegetables, or your favorite crackers or pita bread.
.
Ingredients:
1 Can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained
1 Heaping TBL of Curry Powder (Coconut Curry is delicious if you can find it)
1 Lemon, juiced
1/4 Cup Olive oil
2 Cloves garlic, minced
1-2 TBL. of tahini
Pink salt & pepper to taste
*Filtered water for blending if needed
.
Directions:
1)Rise and drain the can of chickpeas. Boil the chickpeas in water for 5-10 minutes until the chickpeas
are soft and the skins begin to float to the top; rinse, cool, and set aside to cool for 5 mins.
2) In a blender, add the boiled chickpeas and remaining ingredients. Blend until smooth and get desired
consistency. I like to add in additional water to help blend and get smooth consistency - amount varies.
4) Optional: to top with some toppings like red onion, tomatoes, cucumber, and herbs. Enjoy!
.
.
.

Classic steak & potatoes dinner for Friday night! 🥩+🥔+🥦= 🤌 Brent is home for the weekend and wanted to make his favorite.
.
🥩Brent’s Fav Steak situation:
1️⃣Get a skillet nice hot and melt 1 Tbl. of butter.
2️⃣Sear each side 3-4 mins, then finish in a warm oven to finish cooking. (Remove steak and place on a baking sheet). Cooking time depends on how you like your steak - this is for Medium.
3️⃣In the same skillet, melt another Tbl. of butter and sauté 1/2 chopped onion. Sauté for 5 mins.
4️⃣Add 8oz. of sliced or chopped mushrooms + 1/5 cup of water or broth, 1 tsp. Mined garlic, some thyme, and salt & pepper to taste. Cook another 5-7 mins until mushrooms are cooked down. *adding a splash of bourbon here is tasty too. 
5️⃣I remove 1/2 the mushroom mixture for myself and I add blue cheese to the other half and let the blue cheese melt, for Brent.
6️⃣Top mushroom mixture on top of the steak before serving. 
.
🥔Crispy Smashed Potatoes! 
1️⃣First boil, or microwave mini potatoes. (I chose to microwave a bag of mini potatoes; fast & easy.)
2️⃣Spread on a greased baking sheet; smash with a glass jar or whatever you have.
3️⃣Drizzle with olive oil and roast in the oven on 400 for 10ish minutes until edges are golden brown.
4️⃣Remove from oven, sprinkle with pink salt and any other spices you like and you are good to go! Serve with sour cream.
.
🥦Simple steamed broccoli. 
.
Hope y’all have a wonderful weekend! 
.
.
.

How cute are these MINI AHI TUNA POKE LETTUCE WRAPS? 🥬🐟
.
EASY TO MAKE! Minimal ingredients, refreshing, and SO SO GOOD! 
. 
Sushi Grade Ahi Tuna Marinade recipe:
{ 2 servings }
➡️1 package of sushi-grade tuna. Cube & place in a bowl with marinade:
- 1/3 C Coconut aminos { or soy sauce }
- 2 tsp. Sesame seed oil
- 2-3 Tbl. your favorite hot sauce, this time I used @sietefoods Jalapeño hot sauce
➡️Let marinade for at least an hour 🤘🏻
.
I served these with cooked quinoa {mixed in Sriracha + mayo once quinoa cooled} + cucumber + avocado + micro greens + seaweed flakes and sesame seeds.
.
‼️SUSHI-GRADE vs. Regular TUNA STEAK ‼️
👉🏻Sushi-grade will be in the frozen section of your grocery store bc is defined by the temperature it’s kept at after defrosting from the boat. It’s kept just above freezing. Regular fresh tuna steak you see at the market counter has been thawed and no longer considered sushi-grade {can’t eat it raw} and must be seared prior to eating.🐟
.
.
.

Brent requested a simple #smoothierecipe 🥤 here ya go!
.
🍌1/2 frozen banana
🫐1/2 C blueberries ( use any berries you have/love - mix it up for variety )
🥥1/2 C coconut water ( I buy bulk from @costco )
💧1/2 C water
🍃Handful of frozen spinach (optional)
🥜Dollop of nut butter (I used PB)
.
#protip: blend the liquid and berries FIRST until smooth, THEN add in your leafy greens at the end and blend briefly 🌪️Over-blending greens, if using, can make the smoothie frothy - eww. Keeping the greens frozen is helpful too. 
.
For some reason smoothies can get overwhelming. I used to be obsessed with adding ALL the superfoods and protein powders, then I realized less is more. I love having this mid-morning - like a snackitizer to lunch. 😆
.
.
.

So honored to be featured on @susangkomen blog this past week! 💕🎀 Thank you for the opportunity to share my story and express how important EARLY DETECTION truly is. 

Most FAQ: “Did you feel or notice a lump?” ➡️ NO! No, I did not - it was internal, and I felt completely fine. It was detected by my annual mammogram. 

Ladies, if you haven’t scheduled your mammogram this year, now is the time! Don’t push it off.

I am 6 months into my journey and so grateful to now be a survivor. 💪

If you have any questions, or maybe you have recently been diagnosed, OR just need someone who has gone through it to talk to, please reach out. XOXO

https://www.komen.org/blog/ericas-story-early-detection-is-key/

1 Cup oat flour {or simply blend your oats in any blender, I use a #vitamix}

2 Tbl. maple syrup @lakanto

🫑Quinoa, Black Bean & Mango Stuffed Poblano Peppers 😋
.
Ingredients:
- 2 large poblano’s, sliced in half with seeds removed
- 1/2 cup cooked quinoa, I used red quinoa
- 1 cup broth of choice
- 1 cup, canned black beans
- 1/2 cup fresh mango, diced
- 1 TBL olive oil
- 1/2 lime, juiced
- Pink salt & pepper to taste
- Garnish: cilantro, jalapeno hot sauce, I used @sietefoods 
.
Directions:
1️⃣ Prepare the quinoa. Bring broth to a boil and add quinoa. Simmer for 12-15 minutes until fully
cooked.
2️⃣ Turn the heat off and stir black beans, diced mango, lime juice, olive oil, and cilantro.
3️⃣ Set oven to 400; place poblano halves on a baking sheet. Stuff with the quinoa, black bean and
mango mixture. Bake for about 15 minutes.
4️⃣ Remove from the oven, garnish with more cilantro and fresh lime juice, and drizzle of jalapeno hot sauce. Enjoy!
.
.

Sunday #steakdinner ➡️ Garlic & Feta Whipped Potatoes + Steak & an arugula, beet, fig, and blue cheese salad.
.
🥔What you’ll need for the Garlic & Feta Whipped Potatoes:
-3 pounds potatoes of choice ( I used red potatoes and skins on )
-1/2 cup Greek yogurt
-4 cloves garlic, roasted and minced
-2 tsp. red wine vinegar
-1/3 cup feta
-Pink salt & pepper to taste
-parsley for garnish
.
Do it:👇🏻
1️⃣Set oven to 400. Spray and roast cloves of garlic until golden brown. ( about 10-15 minutes) place on cutting board and mince.
2️⃣ Quarter and boil potatoes until tender; strain and add back into the warm pot with remaining ingredients: greek yogurt, minced roasted garlic, feta, red wine vinegar, pink salt & pepper
3️⃣Mix with a hand mixer until combined! Top with chopped parsley and serve.
.
🥩For the steak: season with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Sear on all sides in butter - time depends on how you like your steak. Finish cooking in the oven if needed.
.
.
.

Need something to bake this weekend? Try my GINGERBREAD COOKIES!🎄🍪 Made them next-level by dipping in white chocolate and sprinkled crushed candy cane. 💁🏻‍♀️

Perfect for cookie exchanges, gifts, and of course for Santa. 🎅🏼

GINGERBREAD COOKIES:
🥣Mix WET ingredients in a bowl:👇🏻
-1/2 C nut butter of choice
-1/4 C + 1 Tbl. black strap molasses
-2 eggs

🥣Mix DRY ingredients in another bowl:👇🏻
-1/2 C + 1 Tbl. coconut flour
-1/4 C sugar of choice
-1 tsp. ground ginger
-1 tsp. cinnamon
-1 tsp. all spice
-1 tsp. baking powder
-1/4 tsp. pink salt

1️⃣Combine dry to wet ingredients. {hand-mixer recommended} Store dough in the fridge for an hour. 
2️⃣Roll into balls then roll into mix of coconut sugar or sugar 
3️⃣Place on a baking sheet and flatten with your hand or jar. Bake on 350 for 10-12 mins.

You might want to go ahead a just double the recipe.👌🏻

*optional: Melted white chocolate chips and sprinkled crushed candy canes.
